		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />If you want a good animation program, I'd second ASEprite. I've used it for months and I actually have it open right now working on some character animations. The paid version is a lot more feature-rich, but free version has some benefits like a more beginner-friendly interface and better onion-skinning. It even has some features useful for NES developers, like indexed palette support so you have your NES palette on-hand.

		

